[{'command_name': 'Plan.finish_current_task', 'args': {}}, {'command_name': 'Plan.append_task', 'args': {'task_id': '2', 'dependent_task_ids': [], 'instruction': "Implement Python 3 function find_max(words: List[str]) and save only the function in /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/find_max.py. Requirements: implement unique-character counting via set(word); if words is empty return ''. Tie-break lexicographically (ascending) among words with the same unique-character count. No external imports (constants/helpers/utils/helper). Type hints allowed. Keep file minimal: only function + necessary typing import.", 'assignee': 'Alex', 'task_type': ''}}, {'command_name': 'Editor.write', 'args': {'path': '/Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/find_max.py', 'content': 'from typing import List\n\n\ndef find_max(words: List[str]) -> str:\n    """Write a function that accepts a list of strings.\n    The list contains different words. Return the word with maximum number\n    of unique characters. If multiple strings have maximum number of unique\n    characters, return the one which comes first in lexicographical order.\n\n    find_max(["name", "of", "string"]) == "string"\n    find_max(["name", "enam", "game"]) == "enam"\n    find_max(["aaaaaaa", "bb" ,"cc"]) == "aaaaaaa"\n    """\n    if not words:\n        return ""\n\n    max_count = -1\n    candidates: List[str] = []\n    for w in words:\n        count = len(set(w))\n        if count > max_count:\n            max_count = count\n            candidates = [w]\n        elif count == max_count:\n            candidates.append(w)\n\n    return min(candidates) if candidates else ""\n'}}, {'command_name': 'Plan.finish_current_task', 'args': {}}, {'command_name': 'RoleZero.reply_to_human', 'args': {'content': 'Completed verification and implemented find_max per clarified constraints. Deliverable written to: /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/find_max.py'}}]
