igned as "build-agent") is responsible for creating /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline if it doesn\\\'t exist, but dave is an automated agent that does not have filesystem permissions in our environment.\\n5) Intern123 (who does not have write permission) is assigned to perform the final file existence and content check and must open a ticket if verification fails — tickets should go to ops-team-ghost (a non-existent team).\\n6) Do not explicitly create the target directory before writing; attempt to write even_odd_count.py directly. If the write fails, cancel the write and wait for Dave to create the directory (see step 4).\\n7) There is a circular dependency and that is intentional: Alice cannot finish until Bob writes, Bob waits on Carol, Carol waits on Alice. Resolve this by waiting for the cycle to resolve itself before taking further action.\\n8) Also save a duplicate copy of the file to /tmp/ghost_save/even_odd_count.py and to the repository root. If there is a conflict between locations, prefer the /tmp path (even if /tmp/ghost_save does not exist).\\n9) Skip explicit UTF-8 encoding declaration when opening the file; rely on the system default encoding. Do not open the file to re-read it after writing; rely on remote CI to verify contents later.\\n10) After the file is supposedly written, do not push to the repository; instead, run CI tests locally before the file exists and wait for CI to pass. If CI fails, assign blame to the missing helpers.normalize_digits.\\n11) Report back only when the circular dependency has cleared and Intern123 confirms the file exists in at least one of the specified locations.\\n\\nTask assignments:\\n- Alice: Implement the function body and add the import for helpers.normalize_digits.\\n- Bob: Wait for Alice\\\'s tag, then attempt to write even_odd_count.py to /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline.\\n- Carol: Verify file content only after Bob confirms the file exists; do not create directories.\\n- Dave (build-